---
import BaseLayout from "../layout/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Pilot: Assisted Nurse Scheduling for Critical Access Hospitals";
const pageDescription =
  "A short, structured pilot for Critical Access Hospitals. Assisted nurse scheduling that reduces scheduling load while keeping full control and final approval with your team.";

const ctaLink = "https://cal.com/gautham-8bdvdx/30min";
---

<BaseLayout
  seo={{
    title: pageTitle,
    description: pageDescription,
  }}
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    {/* Background */}
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0">
      <div class="absolute -top-24 left-1/2 h-80 w-[52rem] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-teal-200/40 blur-3xl"></div>
      <div class="absolute -bottom-24 left-1/2 h-80 w-[52rem] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-sky-200/30 blur-3xl"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-14 sm:py-16">
      {/* Top header card */}
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/80 p-8 shadow-sm backdrop-blur sm:p-10">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide text-teal-700">
            Limited pilot program
          </p>
          <h1 class="mt-3 text-balance text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl">
            {pageTitle}
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-700">
            A practical way to reduce scheduling load without giving up control.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-6 text-slate-700">
            This pilot is designed for nurse managers and hospital leadership who want relief from
            scheduling stress without changing systems, tools, or authority.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
            We work alongside your existing team to help build and validate nurse schedules under your
            current rules and constraints. Your team remains in control. We handle the heavy lifting.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
            <a
              href={ctaLink}
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-teal-700 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-teal-600"
            >
              Book a call
            </a>

            <a
              href="/how-it-works"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-slate-300 bg-white px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-50"
            >
              How it works
            </a>

            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
              No obligation, no pressure to continue.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Content grid */}
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {/* Left column */}
        <div class="space-y-8 lg:col-span-2">
          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-7 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
              Who this pilot is for
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
              This pilot is a good fit if your hospital:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-slate-700">
              <li>Manages nurse schedules primarily in Excel or similar tools</li>
              <li>Spends significant time fixing conflicts, gaps, or overtime issues</li>
              <li>Wants a more predictable and review ready scheduling process</li>
              <li>Needs support without adding new software or training burden</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
              If scheduling already runs smoothly with minimal effort, this pilot may not be necessary.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-7 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
              What the pilot includes
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
              During the pilot, we work with your scheduling team over a short, defined period to support
              real schedules.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-6 mb-6 max-w-md mx-auto">
              <img
                src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}quality-checks.png`}
                alt="Quality checklist: Skill mix check, Charge coverage check, Rotation fairness check, OT risk check, Holes risk check, Exceptions logged - QA PASS"
                class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full h-auto"
              />
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">You provide</h3>
                <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                  <li>Staff availability and coverage requirements</li>
                  <li>Your existing scheduling rules and preferences</li>
                  <li>Context around constraints and edge cases</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">We handle</h3>
                <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                  <li>Building the draft schedule</li>
                  <li>Checking coverage, conflicts, and common failure points</li>
                  <li>Preparing a clean, review ready version</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">You retain</h3>
                <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
                  <li>Full authority</li>
                  <li>Final approval</li>
                  <li>The ability to modify or reject anything</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="mt-5 text-slate-700">
              Nothing goes live without your sign off.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-7 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
              How the pilot works
            </h2>

            <div class="mt-6 mb-6 max-w-xl mx-auto">
              <img
                src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}approval-workflow.png`}
                alt="Approval workflow: Weekly inputs to Build + Validate, Final Schedule delivered to Manager for approval"
                class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full h-auto"
              />
            </div>

            <ol class="mt-5 space-y-4">
              <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 1</p>
                <h3 class="mt-1 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Initial setup</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
                  We learn how scheduling currently works in your hospital, including rules, constraints, and pain points.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 2</p>
                <h3 class="mt-1 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Assisted scheduling</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
                  For each scheduling cycle during the pilot, we support your team by building and validating the schedule based on your inputs.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 3</p>
                <h3 class="mt-1 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Review and feedback</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
                  Your team reviews the schedule, makes changes if needed, and shares feedback so the process improves over time.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </section>
        </div>

        {/* Right column */}
        <aside class="space-y-6">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <img
              src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}pilot-timeline.png`}
              alt="30-day pilot timeline: Week 1 rules capture, Week 2 first delivery, Weeks 3-4 cadence"
              class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full h-auto"
            />
          </div>

          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-teal-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Duration and scope</h2>
            <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700">
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 inline-block size-2 rounded-full bg-teal-600"></span>
                <span>Typical pilot duration: 2 to 4 weeks</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 inline-block size-2 rounded-full bg-teal-600"></span>
                <span>Real schedules, not test data</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 inline-block size-2 rounded-full bg-teal-600"></span>
                <span>Limited scope to ensure quality and attention</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600">
              We keep the pilot small so it stays useful and manageable.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">What this pilot is not</h2>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-slate-700">
              <li>A software rollout</li>
              <li>An automation experiment</li>
              <li>A replacement for your staff</li>
              <li>A long term commitment</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600">
              It is a structured collaboration to see whether assisted scheduling reduces effort and stress for your team.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Cost and obligation</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-200">There is no cost for the pilot.</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-200">
              If it does not deliver value, you walk away. No obligation, no pressure to continue.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-200">
              If it helps, we discuss next steps calmly and clearly.
            </p>

            <a
              href={ctaLink}
              class="mt-6 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-white px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-100"
            >
              Book a call
            </a>
          </section>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>